- Blorpticate(y,z) means y and z are disconnected and share no spatial parts

Now I'll check each possible relation between x and z:

2. Snarfloon(x,z): If x and z touch only at their boundaries, this is consistent because y doesn't touch x's boundary, so y and z remain disconnected.

4. Glimberish(z,x): If z is part of x and touches x's boundary, this is possible as long as z doesn't overlap with y inside x.

5. Crindlewop(z,x): If z is part of x but doesn't touch x's boundary, this works as long as z doesn't overlap with y inside x.

6. Narpulate(x,z): This is the same as Glimberish(z,x), so it's possible.

7. Zindlequack(x,z): This is the same as Crindlewop(z,x), so it's possible.

Frooblenap(x,z) is not possible because if x and z were coincident, then y would have to be part of z, contradicting Blorpticate(y,z).
